cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC. 

The paper proposes a collaborative task that involves language, perception, and action, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on language and communication in the task makes cs.CL the most likely sub-category. The use of machine learning models to play the game and the evaluation metrics also suggest that it could belong to cs.AI and cs.LG. The use of images and clip art pieces in the game could also make it relevant to cs.CV. Finally, the emphasis on human-computer interaction and the collection of a dataset of human-human interactions suggest that it could belong to cs.HC.
